description:
Bug 38131: ajc needs -d option. I am using version 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and different from javac. I suspect this issue is related to a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler. To reproduce the problem:
1. Create a class in a subpackage, for example:
package subpackage;

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}
2. Compile the class using the following command:
   ajc subpackage\Test.java

OB: The compiled Test.class file is placed in a subpackage\subpackage directory, resulting in the following error when running the java command:
   Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: subpackage/Test

EB: The Test class should be placed directly under the subpackage directory, and therefore the java command should run successfully without any errors.

SR: To fix the problem, use the following command instead:
   ajc -d . subpackage\Test.java
